==English==

=== Etymology ===
Old English ''græs'', from Germanic, from the same Proto-Indo-European root as [[grow]] and [[green]].

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: grăs
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: (British) /graːs/, (US) /græs/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: (British) /grA:s/, (US) /gr{s/
*{{audio|en-uk-grass.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

=== Noun ===
'''grass'''

# Any [[plant]] of the [[family]] [[Poaceae]], characterized by [[leaves]] that arise from [[node]]s in the [[stem]], wrap around it for a distance, and leave, especially those grown as [[ground cover]] rather than for [[grain]]. 
# a [[lawn]].
# {{slang}} [[marijuana]].
# {{slang}} [[Informer]], police informer; one who betrays a group (of criminals, etc) to the authorities.

